{
  "texts": [
    "The inprocess EU AI Act (AIA) not only attempts to define Gen AI but also contains specific provisions for it (Barani & Van Dyck, 2023), such as efforts to curtail IPR infringement and restrict manipulative, deepfake content.",
    "Lee, Lucchini, and Lee (2024) predict that both the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), in effect since 2018, and the AIA, which entered into force in August 2024, will transform the Gen AI market.",
    "Accordingly, we call for research into the likely impacts of current and proposed regulations on Gen AI advancement, proliferation, and innovation.",
    "Second, investigations of the longer-term societal impact of Gen AI will be helpful.",
    "Considering its exponential growth, Gen AI is likely to continue to advance in the coming years."
  ]
}